
<p>I put out a video <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bwJBCfpFT_E" target="_blank">here</a> on getting random numbers and randomizing files in the Linux command line. I talk about:</p>

<ul>
	<li>/dev/urandom/</li>
	<li><code>$RANDOM</code> in bash</li>
	<li><code>shuf</code> in GNU/Linux</li>
</ul>

<p>Check it out! I don't think I mentioned it, but <code>shuf</code> can also take standard input!</p>
